pros:
* Scale! In Google you can improve the products used by billions of people, or shape the future of the entire industry. Few companies can boast that;
* Outstanding developer and production infrastructure;
* Great culture and supportive peers;
* Tech management done right - usually your managers are your senior peers who are incredibly helpful and have first-hand knowledge of your area;
* Good compensation and perks.

cons:
* Things may move slowly - even the smallest changes and experiments take a long time;
* In established and seasoned products, your contributions might look small and negligible at first;
* You mostly work with internal tools, and have no idea what's happening in the wild.
